run into the filter either.

out of well water.

with minerals in the water.

To generation.

Well, the best thing, one of the best things I've always noticed is your cattle or your goats or your sheep.
You take an old goat, and if you're going to have an orther,
You just get out and look at them and see what they're doing.
Every one of them will hit a beeline right straight to the north.
That wind blows that hair right back on their bodies.
And they'll hit, there'll be a bluff or there'll be a shed or there'll be something.
And they'll go right straight to it.
To the north.
They'll face the north because that blows their fur back against their body rather than away where it gets to their skin.
And you watch a cattle lie down early in the morning.
If they point that head towards the north, you know what's coming.
There's going to be cold weather that one of the fronts will be coming through.
One of the fronts.
You just...
You watch your animals, and you'll see.
You watch an old hog, and they'll go out and gather up sticks and things and build a nest, or we call it a nest, but build a bed in the corner of the pen.
When you see them doing that, you know what's going to happen.
What?
It's going to be colder than Hades.
Really?
And that's just as regular as clockwork.
Uh-huh.
Uh-huh.
It's, well...

always was with us and helped us.
